The article discusses the main points and outcomes of the 2014 G-7 Summit in Brussels. The G-7 leaders met to discuss the situation in Ukraine and to show support for the country's efforts to build a stronger democracy. They also discussed their commitment to imposing economic costs on Russia for its interference in Ukraine. The G-7 leaders pledged to support Ukraine in its reform efforts and to provide financial assistance. The article also highlights the importance of energy security and climate action, with the G-7 leaders agreeing to enhance energy security and take concrete action on climate change. The leaders also discussed development priorities, including global health security, support for the GAVI Alliance and the Global Fund, and food security and nutrition. The article concludes by emphasizing the importance of an ambitious and universal post-2015 development agenda.